p Conventional wisdom asserts that mania is excessive fight <em>and</em> flight and should be treated with sedatives so you will no longer be manic whereas depression is excessive rest <em>and</em> refuel and should be treated with stimulants so you will no longer be depressed.
p The BipolarType theory asserts that mania is excessive fight <em>or</em> flight and should be treated by doing more of one of the adjacent behaviors so you will no longer be <em>unbalanced</em>. Similarly, depression is excessive rest <em>or</em> refuel and should be treated by doing more of one of the adjacent behaviors.
p Which of the adjacent behaviors you can switch to depends on which Mood you are in.
p If, for example, you are manic and fleeing too much, you may be in either #{link_to_concept Mood.e} or #{link_to_concept Mood.p}. In the first case you can stop fleeing and move on to fighting, in the second you can stop fleeing and go back to refueling. You cannot, however stop fleeing and <em>rest</em> without taking sedatives.
